description: Temagami is home to thousands of lakes and rivers in northern Ontario. This map covers the Northeast quadrant, from Maple Mountain to the west, Latchford and Hwy 11 to the east, Wakimika Lake, Sandy Inlet and Red Squirrel Road to the south and the Spray Creek/Big Spring Lake/Montreal River junction to the north. Includes information on campsites, portages, public hiking trails, access points, historical features, primary fish species by lake, lake elevations, access roads, and island numbers, and shows 20m contours.
name: Adventure Map Temagami 1 - Northeast Map
